properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued January 29 at 10:31AM AKST until January 30 at 4:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Winds gusting as high as
45 to 60 mph. Total snow accumulations of 4 to 10 inches with
locally higher amounts.

* WHERE...Whittier, Portage Valley, Eastern Turnagain Arm, and
Turnagain Pass.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 4 AM AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult. Blowing snow will
reduce visibilities to one quarter mile or less at times.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will fall all day. Strong and gusty
winds will rapidly develop in mid afternoon. While the worst
conditions will be the eastern Turnagain Arm area, low
visibilities in snow and blowing snow will affect the entire
Seward Highway corridor from eastern Turnagain Arm to Seward.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 4 AM AKST THURSDAY FOR WHITTIER TO EASTERN TURNAGAIN ARM AND TURNAGAIN PASS...
